Building
--------

The environment variable OBJECTCODE has to be set to one of the 
compiler choices given in config/. When using CARRE2 in the SOLPS environment, 
the OBJECTCODE variable is usually set by the SOLPS setup scripts.

Examples: 

For tcsh:
 
 setenv OBJECTCODE amd64_gfortran_4.6.debug

For bash:

 export OBJECTCODE=amd64_gfortran_4.6.debug

Alternatively, one can inject it in the Makefile by

 make OBJECTCODE=amd64_gfortran_4.6.debug <target>


To build, execute the following commands:

 make depend
 make 

